This paper discusses the challenges of parallelism and performance management in multi-physics scientific software, which is relevant to several sub-categories. The focus on software design and methodologies suggests cs.SE and cs.MS as likely categories. The mention of hardware architecture and parallelism points towards cs.DC and cs.AR. Finally, the application of these concepts to engineering and scientific simulations suggests cs.CE as a possible category.
